hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Hubble parameter and rms velocity  
   $$H(a)=H_0\sqrt{\Omega_{m,0}}\,a^{-3/2},$$  
   $$v_{\rm rms}=\sqrt{\langle v^2\rangle}
   =\sqrt{\frac{3k_B\,T_\nu(a)}{m_\nu}}
   =\sqrt{\frac{3k_B\,T_{\nu,0}}{m_\nu\,a}}\,. $$

2. Physical free-streaming scale  
   $$\lambda_{\rm phys}=\frac{a}{k_{FS}}\,. $$

3. Equate thermal and Hubble velocities  
   $$v_{\rm rms}=H(a)\,\lambda_{\rm phys} 
   \;\Longrightarrow\;
   \sqrt{\frac{3k_B\,T_{\nu,0}}{m_\nu\,a}}
   =H_0\sqrt{\Omega_{m,0}}\,a^{-3/2}\,\frac{a}{k_{FS}}\,. $$

4. Simplify and solve for $k_{FS}$  
   Left side: $\sqrt{\frac{3k_B\,T_{\nu,0}}{m_\nu\,a}}
   =\sqrt{\frac{3k_B\,T_{\nu,0}}{m_\nu}}\,a^{-1/2}$.  
   Right side: $H_0\sqrt{\Omega_{m,0}}\,a^{-1/2}/k_{FS}$.  
   Cancel $a^{-1/2}$ and invert  
   $$\sqrt{\frac{3k_B\,T_{\nu,0}}{m_\nu}}
   =\frac{H_0\sqrt{\Omega_{m,0}}}{k_{FS}}
   \;\Longrightarrow\;
   k_{FS}
   =H_0\sqrt{\frac{\Omega_{m,0}\,m_\nu}{3\,k_B\,T_{\nu,0}}}\,. $$
